@Node Main "Readme.guide"



                             TRASHMASTER V1.7

           The @{i}ultimate@{ui} in byte disposal for the Amiga.

          Copyright (C) 1994 By Aric R Caley and Greywire designs

                                4 July 1994

   In short, this a "super trashcan" that deletes icons dropped into it, as
opposed to the normal trashcan that is simply a directory on the disk.
And, unlike some other similar programs, Trashmaster makes sure Workbench
properly removes its icons..even if they are icons that Workbench made on
the fly with the @{b}Show  » All Files@{ub} option.

   There are other programs out there, that try to do exactly the same
thing.  I don't know if any of us have copied from each other, we just all
had the same basic idea.  However, Trashmaster is much better than anything
I've yet seen - its smaller (no big deal, though), and it handles things
better.  For instance, none of them seem to properly delete files if the
icon is a "fake" icon created by the Workbench @{b}Show » All Files@{ub} option
(the icon never goes away).


