Trashmaster features
********************

   Features of Trashmaster are as follows:

   @{b}*@{ub} It's really small.  In fact, the docs are bigger!

   @{b}*@{ub} It's for 2.0 and above only.

   @{b}*@{ub} It removes any file that Workbench lets you "drag and drop".

   @{b}*@{ub} If the file has a real icon on disk, it is deleted.

   @{b}*@{ub} Workbench removes the icon and closes any windows those icons might
     have open.

   @{b}*@{ub} If Workbench had the @{b}Show  » All Files@{ub} option on, even the "fake"
     icons generated dynamicly will be removed from display.

   @{b}*@{ub} If the file can't be deleted (another program locked it or maybe it
     has an assignment to it), Trashmaster will put the icon back.

   @{b}*@{ub} You can delete things interactively - confirming each file to be either
     deleted, to skip and go to the next file, to delete the rest of the
     files non-interactively or finaly to abort the whole thing.

   @{b}*@{ub} You can format disks.

   @{b}*@{ub} You can force-delete protected files.

   @{b}*@{ub} You can turn off the anoying verification requesters.

   @{b}*@{ub} It's localized.


