Future and History
******************

FUTURE
======

   I intend to write more utilities like this one, that use AppIcons.  I've
recently rewrote my very old SlideMaster, it now uses an AppIcon to display
pictures (in addition to ARexx, command line and old style Workbench
support).  I also have several ideas for extensions to Workbench and
intuition in general ('Encino' - Workbench Replacement).  Eventualy, I will
finish my Interface builder program.  Stay tuned.

   Possible future additions to TrashMaster:

   @{b}*@{ub} CLI command, that works like the Delete command, but also deletes
     icons and makes Workbench remove them from display.

   @{b}*@{ub} "Trash Management".  Options to place files into trashcans, periodic
     "trash collection" to delete older files in the trashcans, etc.

   @{b}*@{ub} Preferences editor (although setting ToolTypes is pretty easy, so this
     is not a high priority item right now).

   @{b}*@{ub} "Wipe"  option  -  writes  0's throughout deleted files to ensure the
     data cannot be recovered.  Might be usefull for security reasons.

   I've had a few people suggest some of these things (as well as some of
things in the latest version).  The more "yays" I hear on these or other
suggestions, the more likely I will spend time implementing them.  So
please speak up if you like what you see.

HISTORY:
========

   (I only had sporadic access to a 2.0 machine, so thats why the versions
are so far apart for such little changes; and/or I had other more pressing
projects to handle first :)

@{b}V1.0 Jan 23 1992.@{ub}
     First release, version 1.0.

@{b}V1.1 Jan 24 1992.@{ub}
     (duh, that didnt take long, did it?  :) Made it "detach" - more
     convienient (didnt think of it before..  duh) and put in the
     needed-but-forgot @{b}DONOTWAIT@{ub} in the icon (for WBStartup)

@{b}V1.2 May 11 1992.@{ub}
     Added "X" and "Y" tooltypes for setting the location of the AppIcon.

@{b}V1.3 Mar 17 1993.@{ub}
     Added @{b}ICON@{ub} tooltype.

@{b}V1.4 Apr 27 1993.@{ub}
     Added interactive option, fixed minor bug - forgot to free a message
     port.

@{b}V1.5 Jul 5 1993.@{ub}
     Better handling of protected files - with "force" requester, and @{b}FORCE@{ub}
     tooltype.  Now formats disks when dropped on us.  Added @{b}NAME@{ub} tooltype
     to specify the AppIcon's name.  Added @{b}VERIFY@{ub} tooltype to turn off the
     verification requester.  Added @{b}TYPE@{ub} tooltype to control the default
     delete mode when @{b}VERIFY@{ub} is used.  Fixed bug that caused a crash if you
     renamed Trashmaster, fixed bug that wouldn't delete a file in a
     directory if it had only an .info file.

@{b}V1.6 Jul 28 1993.@{ub}
     Fixed a bug that prevented Trashmaster from working on some systems
     (About requester always quit Trashmaster; no files were deleted no
     matter what option was selected from verify requester)

@{b}V1.7@{ub}
     Added localization (need some translations, though).  Icons don't blink
     when deleted, and when in "view by name" mode the names blink only
     twice (Workbench "bug" I guess) instead of four times.  Command line
     options.


